## âœ… Where you *can* get data: ERA5 reanalysis

* The ERA5 reanalysis dataset provides monthly-averaged (and hourly) data of global atmospheric variables â€” including **sea-level pressure (SLP)** â€” from 1940 to present. ([Climate Data Store][1])
* You (or any researcher) can download SLP over the Bay of Bengal region via the Copernicus Climate Data Store (CDS) using their web interface or API. ([ECMWF Confluence][2])
* Once you have gridded data (e.g. at 0.25Â° Ã— 0.25Â° resolution), you can compute spatial derivatives (pressure gradients) by finite-difference in latitude/longitude (or using specialized analysis tools â€” e.g. Python + xarray, NCL, Ferret, CDO, etc.).

